<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochilidae" genus="Ectatosticta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ectatosticta" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Ectatosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marx" authorityYear="1888" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochilidae" genus="Hypochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hypochilus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hypochilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the rectangular labium which is almost as long as wide and bears a pair of triangular posterolateral flanges, also by numerous leg spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, RR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 116" refId="B2" refString="Forster, RR, Platnick, NI, Gray, MR, 1987. A review of the spider superfamilies Hypochiloidea and Austrochiloidea (Araneae, Araneomorphae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 185: 1 - 116" title="A review of the spider superfamilies Hypochiloidea and Austrochiloidea (Araneae, Araneomorphae)." volume="185" year="1987">Forster et al. 1987</bibRefCitation>
) and in the lateral view of the male palp, the cymbium to bulb length ratio is almost 3:1 (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Ectatosticta spp., prolateral view of left male palps A E. davidi, male from Shaanxi B E. deltshevi, holotype C E. wukong sp. nov., holotype D E. wukong sp. nov., embolus and conductor of right palp (rotated horizontally), holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.954.52254.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/436974" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Ectatosticta spp., retrolateral view of left male palps A E. davidi, male from Shaanxi B E. deltshevi, holotype C E. wukong sp. nov., holotype D E. wukong sp. nov., embolus and conductor of right palp (rotated horizontally), holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.954.52254.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/436976" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4</figureCitation>
) but nearly 1: 1 in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marx" authorityYear="1888" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochilidae" genus="Hypochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hypochilus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Hypochilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Forster, RR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 116" refId="B2" refString="Forster, RR, Platnick, NI, Gray, MR, 1987. A review of the spider superfamilies Hypochiloidea and Austrochiloidea (Araneae, Araneomorphae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 185: 1 - 116" title="A review of the spider superfamilies Hypochiloidea and Austrochiloidea (Araneae, Araneomorphae)." volume="185" year="1987">Forster et al. 1987</bibRefCitation>
: figs 38, 43, 48, 53, 58, 63, 68, 73).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
